oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SUSY with R-symmetry: confronting EW precision observables and LHC constraints
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Kalinowski, Jan
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: High Energy Physics - Phenomenology
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: After motivation and short presentation of the minimal supersymmetric model with R-symmetry (MRSSM), we address the question of accomodating the measured Higgs boson mass in accordance with electroweak precision observables and LHC constraints.
Comment: 13 pages, 3 figures, lecture given at the 55th Cracow School of Theoretical Physics, June 20-28, 2015, Zakopane, Poland. In print in Acta Physica Polonica
